---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageShell from '../../components/system/PageShell.astro';
import Badge from '../../components/system/Badge.astro';
import ActionLink from '../../components/system/ActionLink.astro';
import { ArrowUpRight, Mail } from '@lucide/astro';
---

<Layout>
  <PageShell class="about-shell">
    <header class="page-header">
      <Badge tone="accent">About Emmanuel</Badge>
      <h1>I build to understand. I break to learn.</h1>
      <p class="lead">I am Emmanuel Awe, known online as COCOFELON. My work sits between software engineering, offensive security, and the financial systems where small assumptions can become expensive problems.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="content-grid">
      <section class="prose-block">
        <p>I did not arrive at security by staying outside the system. I kept building things: APIs, tools, automation, experiments, and finance-shaped workflows. The more I built, the more I wanted to understand what happened when trust was misplaced or state was allowed to drift.</p>
        <p>That curiosity took me into exploit research, cloud identity, application logic, Windows internals, and the uncomfortable space between what software is supposed to do and what it actually permits.</p>
        <p>I write about that work because a vulnerability is rarely just a clever trick. It is usually a design decision, an assumption, or a missing conversation showing up late.</p>
      </section>

      <aside class="identity-note">
        <p class="eyebrow">Names are part of the work</p>
        <p>Many of my repositories carry biblical names. Jericho, Beulah, and the others are not branding exercises. They give the work a memory: walls, belonging, stewardship, struggle, and becoming.</p>
      </aside>
    </div>

    <section class="principles" aria-labelledby="principles-title">
      <p class="eyebrow">How I work</p>
      <h2 id="principles-title">Build the system. Trace the trust. Explain the failure.</h2>
      <div class="principle-list">
        <article><span>01</span><div><h3>Systems first</h3><p>I learn the architecture before making claims about the bug.</p></div></article>
        <article><span>02</span><div><h3>Evidence over theatre</h3><p>Research should show what happened, what mattered, and what changes next.</p></div></article>
        <article><span>03</span><div><h3>Responsible practice</h3><p>Exploit experience belongs inside clear permission, controlled testing, and useful disclosure.</p></div></article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-block">
      <div><p class="eyebrow">Keep in touch</p><h2>Bring me a system worth understanding.</h2></div>
      <div class="contact-actions"><ActionLink href="mailto:hello@cocofelon.lol" variant="primary"><Mail size={15} aria-hidden="true" /> Email me</ActionLink><ActionLink href="https://github.com/ITEKONGIT"><ArrowUpRight size={15} aria-hidden="true" /> GitHub</ActionLink></div>
    </section>
  </PageShell>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-shell { max-width: 980px; }
  .page-header { max-width: 760px; padding: 1.5rem 0 3rem; }
  h1 { margin-top: 1rem; color: var(--text); font-size: clamp(2.3rem, 10vw, 5.2rem); line-height: 1; letter-spacing: 0; }
  .lead, .prose-block p, .identity-note p:not(.eyebrow), .principle-list p { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.96rem; font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.8; }
  .lead { margin-top: 1rem; }
  .content-grid { display: grid; gap: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-muted); padding-top: 1.35rem; }
  .prose-block { display: grid; gap: 1rem; max-width: 670px; }
  .identity-note { align-self: start; padding: 1rem; border-left: 1px solid var(--accent); background: var(--surface-soft); }
  .identity-note p:not(.eyebrow) { margin-top: 0.7rem; color: var(--text); font-size: 0.86rem; }
  .eyebrow { color: var(--accent); font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.58rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  h2 { margin-top: 0.55rem; color: var(--text); font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 6vw, 2.7rem); line-height: 1.08; letter-spacing: 0; }
  .principles { margin-top: 4.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-muted); padding-top: 1.35rem; }
  .principle-list { display: grid; gap: 0; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .principle-list article { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2rem 1fr; gap: 0.8rem; padding: 1rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-muted); }
  .principle-list span { color: var(--accent); font: 0.58rem 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }
  h3 { color: var(--text); font-size: 1.02rem; letter-spacing: 0; }
  .principle-list p { margin-top: 0.25rem; font-size: 0.82rem; }
  .contact-block { display: grid; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 4.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-muted); padding-top: 1.35rem; }
  .contact-actions { display: grid; gap: 0.7rem; }
  @media (min-width: 700px) { .page-header { padding-top: 4rem; padding-bottom: 5rem; } .content-grid { grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) 280px; gap: 4rem; } .contact-block { grid-template-columns: 1fr auto; align-items: end; } .contact-actions { display: flex; } }
</style>
